DESCRIPTION:   
Velocity Works is proud to offer the custom-built VW Sniper Mosin Nagant. 

The objective of this custom-built rifle was to produce a capable and attractive heavy caliber, long-range precision target rifle that fires inexpensive ammo and can be had for hundreds less than an off-the-shelf item in the same category. 

We started with a conventional 91-30 round-receiver Mosin Nagant.  We then removed the action and barrel from the wood stock, and completely degreased, cleaned, inspected, and function checked the firearm.  All the steel was then polished and professionally hot blued on site to bring out the luster of the steel and protect from corrosion. 

For mounting optics, we went with a top-of-the-line picatinny scope mount.  These heavy duty mounts are precision machined out of 6061 aluminum here in the USA.  The mount utilizes 3 mounting points and has a hard coating to resist chips, scratches and corrosion.  These mounts have been tested up to 800 yards with sub-MOA results, quite impressive considering the kick of a 7.62x54R round.  We had the mount professionally installed by our on-sight gunsmith, who measures, fits the parts, and drills and taps the necessary holes to secure the mount. Included with the mount is a custom down-turned bolt handle which allows the clearance to move freely under the scope.  The bolt handle and body were polished to a high-shine finish. 

For optics we mounted a Sniper Precision Optics 4-16x50mm scope.  Features include a red or green illuminated reticle, locking windage and elevation adjustments, and a removable sun shade. 

To increase the precision of the platform, we installed a Timney Trigger on the receiver.  The light, crisp, 2.5 lb pull has to be felt to be believed.  The action was then fit and installed into a Pro Mag Archangel Mosin Nagant stock.  This new-age, ergonomically friendly, composite stock features a fully adjustable length-of-pull and cheek rest, a small storage compartment, and accepts the included 5-round detachable magazine (10-round mags are available as well).  A Caldwell tilting bipod rounds out the whole package. 

Each of these rifles is fully tested and absolutely ready to fire and enjoy.  If you are looking for a time-tested, heavy caliber, attractive, long range precision target rifle that fires cheap and readily available ammunition while costing hundreds less than the alternatives, purchase one now, or contact us about building one of these custom rifles for you!

title: For Sale:  LCP 380 like new
postcontent:
LCP 380 like new comes with 4 clips with extend ends on them, one soft case, one right side holster, and a really cool wallet hoister that you can put it in your pants like a wallet and remove from your paints and fire it with out removing it from the wallet holster call Joe at REDACTED $450 or trade for ??
One of the many new models that made its debut this year is the LC380. The Ruger LCP has been a huge hit in the modern-day concealed-carry market, but even its fans didn’t think it was perfect. The frame was just too small to get all your fingers on it, and the sights…well, some LCP owners might be surprised to hear their pistols actually have sights.

While the capacity of the LC380 stays the same (7+1), recoil will be less. Being chambered in a less powerful cartridge, the recoil spring for the LC380 is lighter, so the slide is easier to rack. If you are small or weak, buying a gun whose slide you can’t rack or which hurts you every time you shoot it does not encourage regular practice sessions. The .380 you have with you, and have practiced shooting, is better than the 9mm you don’t.

This new gun also allows Ruger to sell a .380 ACP in certain places it couldn’t before because the LC380 has more safety features than the LCP; more on that later.
The LC380 is a bit big for a .380 ACP but still small enough to fit in most pockets. It is 6.0 inches long, 4.5 inches high, and only 0.9 inch wide. It weighs 17.2 ounces unloaded.
